
                                                        +-------+
                                                        |  .H0  |
                                                        +-------+

HEADING LEVEL  "N" formats  the specified  heading into  the text
area and/or adds it to the current Table of Contents.

     +-------+---------------------------------------------+
     |       |                                             |
     |  .H0  |                                             |
     |   to  |    line                                     |
     |  .H9  |                                             |
     |       |                                             |
     +-------+---------------------------------------------+

The .H0 to .H9 control words  are short form commands for Heading
Level (.HL) with an operand of 0 to 9.  These control words cause
a break.  See Heading Level (.HL) for all the information.

<.U+>EXAMPLES<.NORMAL>
(1) .h1 This is a level-one heading
    This control word is equivalent to:
    .hl 1 This is a level-one heading

